A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Captain Matthew T. Brown upon his retirement; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Captain Matthew T. Brown has served with honor and distinction as a member
4 of the Cobb County Police Department for more than 30 years; and
5 WHEREAS, during his distinguished tenure, Captain Brown has worked as part of vital
6 departments such as the Crimes Against Persons Unit, Crimes Against Children Unit, Special
7 Victims Unit, and Major Crimes Unit; and
8 WHEREAS, he has further dedicated innumerable hours of his time and energy toward
9 volunteering with the SafePath Children's Advocacy Center Inc., ensuring that the youth of
10 Cobb County are protected from abuse; and
11 WHEREAS, he is an honest and dedicated public servant who strives for excellence in all
12 of his endeavors and whose primary concern is the welfare and safety of the citizens of Cobb
13 County; and
