14 WHEREAS, this spirited law enforcement professional has exhibited extraordinary devotion
15 to duty, outstanding loyalty, fine leadership, and meticulous attention to detail in all of his
16 duties; and
17 WHEREAS, Captain Brown's efficient and effective commitment to excellence has been
18 recognized by his peers through the many decorations and awards he has received, including
19 a Medal of Valor, the 300 Club Award, and the Chief's Award; and
20 WHEREAS, his inspiring commitment to the welfare of others is an outstanding example of
21 the positive effect law enforcement professionals have on the lives and well-being of others;
22 and
23 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that gratitude is expressed for the unique and
24 often unheralded contributions of local law enforcement professionals on behalf of the
25 citizens of this state.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
27 the members of this body recognize and commend Captain Matthew T. Brown upon the
28 grand occasion of his retirement for his efficient, effective, and dedicated service to Cobb
29 County as well as express their utmost appreciation for having so purely and truly defined
30 for others the meaning of public servant.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
32 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
33 Captain Matthew T. Brown.
